# Laravel Implementation Standards (Mandatory)

Apply these standards whenever implementing or refactoring backend/server-side code in this repository.

## 1) PHP Coding Standard

- Follow PSR-12 style for all PHP files.
- Keep naming clear and consistent (`camelCase` methods/variables, meaningful names).
- Prefer clean, maintainable code over clever shortcuts.

## 2) Module Structure

- Follow the existing Laravel app-layer structure used in this project (`app/Http`, `app/Services`, `app/Repositories`, `app/Models`, `routes`, `database`).
- Place new backend code in the corresponding existing layer with correct namespace conventions; do not introduce a `Modules/<ModuleName>` structure unless explicitly requested.

## 3) Server-Side Contracts and Views

- Add explicit return types where applicable.
- Add PHPDoc with `@return` for server-side methods when it improves contract clarity.
- If feature scope includes web UI rendering, provide corresponding Blade templates/views.

## 4) Reuse and Common Logic

- Avoid duplicating logic across modules/classes.
- Extract shared logic into reusable/common services/helpers/components when truly shared.

## 5) Database Delivery

- Any DB schema change must include migration.
- Provide corresponding seeder/factory setup when test/setup data is needed.
- Keep DB documentation synchronized in `docs/databases_docs/` when mapping/schema changes.
